cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO

This paper involves machine learning and deep learning-based models to automate the interaction with proof assistants. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with software engineering aspects of proof assistants, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category. The paper also involves programming languages and abstract syntax trees, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with logic and theorem proving, which makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible category.
